In this paper we prove a homological stability theorem for the diffeomorphism groups of high dimensional manifolds with boundary, with respect to forming the boundary connected sum with the product $D^{p+1}	imes S^{q}$ for $|q - p| < \min\{p, q\} - 2$. The main theorem is analogous to an earlier paper of the same author that proves a homological stability theorem for the diffeomorphism group of a manifold with respect to forming the connected sum with the product of spheres $S^{p}	imes S^{q}$ (see arXiv:1408.1903 ). In a recent joint paper with Boris Botvinnik (see arXiv:1509.03359 ), we identify the homology of $colim_{g	o \infty}BDiff((D^{n+1}	imes S^{n})^{
atural g}, \; D^{2n})$ with that of the infinite loopspace $Q_{0}BO(2n+1)\langle nangle_{+}$, in the case that $n \geq 4$. By combining this "stable homology" calculation with the results of this current paper we may compute the (co)homology groups of $BDiff((D^{n+1}	imes S^{n})^{
atural g}, D^{2n})$ in degrees $k \leq 	frac{1}{2}(g - 4)$. This leads to the determination of the characteristic classes in degrees $k \leq 	frac{1}{2}(g - 4)$ for all smooth fibre-bundles with fibre diffeomorphic to $(D^{n+1}	imes S^{n})^{
atural g}$.
